==Vive Ut Vivas==
'''Vive Ut Vivas''' is a latin phrase meaning "live that you may live" or simply "live to the fullest." It is popular as a family motto [http://www.proz.com/kudoz/77542]. An alternate translation is "live that you may live forever" [http://www.family-crests.com/coat-of-arms-library/family-crest/translation-motto.html]. The phrase essentially means that one should live life to the fullest and without fear of a possible future consequnce.